msContents.summary: Notes of Christopher Heydrick, a student at the University of Pennsylvania circa 1790, taken from the lectures of William Shippen on anatomy. Topics include the definition and origin of anatomy, blood, glands, nerves, reproductive organs, bones, lungs, and heart.

supportDesc.extent: 100 leaves : 201 x 162 mm. bound to 207 x 179 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, vi + 92 + ii; signatures A-M every sixth leaf beginning on f. 19; [1-92]; modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 22 long lines; ruling in red occasionally visible; catchwords at the bottom of each page.

binding.p: Late eighteenth- or early nineteenth-century quarter calf; upper cover detached.
